.TH Search API docs offline, in your terminal or browser
.PP
dasht is a collection of shell scripts for searching, browsing, and managing
API documentation (in the form of 150+ offline documentation sets \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash#docsets\[ra],
courtesy of Dash for OS X \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash\[ra]) all from the comfort of your own terminal!
.PP
The name "dasht" is a portmanteau of Dash \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash\[ra] and the letter "t", for terminal.
Etymologically, "dasht" is Persian for \fIplain\fP, as in an flat expanse of land,
which aptly characterizes the terminal environment where everything is text.
.SH Features
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
You never have to leave your terminal!
.IP \(bu 2
Local search engine for web browsers.
.IP \(bu 2
Keep Dash \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash\[ra] docsets anywhere you like.
.RE
.SS Preview
.PP
Watch the "dasht in a terminal \[la]https://vimeo.com/159462598\[ra]"
and "dasht in a browser \[la]https://vimeo.com/159462774\[ra]" screencasts.
.PP
[In your terminal](\[la]https://github.com/sunaku/dasht/raw/gh-pages/terminal.png\[ra])
[In your browser](\[la]https://github.com/sunaku/dasht/raw/gh-pages/browser.png\[ra])
.SH Dependencies
.PP
Required:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
POSIX \[la]http://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/\[ra] environment (Linux, BSD, etc.)
.IP \(bu 2
sqlite3 \[la]https://www.sqlite.org/cli.html\[ra] to search inside Dash \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash\[ra] docsets
.RE
.PP
Optional:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
wget \[la]https://www.gnu.org/software/wget/\[ra] to download docsets \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash#docsets\[ra] from Dash \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash\[ra]
.IP \(bu 2
w3m \[la]http://w3m.sourceforge.net/\[ra] to display 
.BR dasht (1) 
search results
.IP \(bu 2
socat \[la]http://www.dest-unreach.org/socat/\[ra] for 
.BR dasht-server (1) 
search engine
.RE
.PP
Development:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
binman \[la]https://sunaku.github.io/binman/\[ra] and md2man \[la]https://sunaku.github.io/md2man/\[ra] to build manual pages
.PP
.RS
.nf
gem install binman md2man
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SH Installation
.PP
In Arch Linux:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Install dasht \[la]https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/dasht/\[ra] or
dasht\-git \[la]https://aur.archlinux.org/packages/dasht-git/\[ra] from the AUR,
maintained by Christian HÃ¶ppner \[la]https://github.com/mkaito\[ra]\&.
.RE
.PP
In macOS using Homebrew \[la]https://brew.sh\[ra]:
.PP
.RS
.nf
brew install dasht
.fi
.RE
.PP
On any system:
.nr step0 0 1
.RS
.IP \n+[step0]
Download \[la]https://github.com/sunaku/dasht/releases\[ra] a stable release or clone \[la]https://github.com/sunaku/dasht.git\[ra] this Git repository.
.IP \n+[step0]
Add the \fB\fCbin/\fR folder to your \fB\fCPATH\fR environment variable:
.PP
.RS
.nf
export PATH=$PATH:location_where_you_cloned_or_downloaded_dasht/bin
.fi
.RE
.IP \n+[step0]
Add the \fB\fCman/\fR folder to your \fB\fCMANPATH\fR environment variable:
.PP
.RS
.nf
export MANPATH=location_where_you_cloned_or_downloaded_dasht/man:$MANPATH
.fi
.RE
.RE
.SS Vim integration
.PP
Use the vim\-dasht \[la]https://github.com/sunaku/vim-dasht\[ra] plugin for (Neo)Vim.
.SS ZSH integration
.PP
Source this file in ZSH to activate TAB completion for dasht:
.PP
.RS
.nf
source location_where_you_cloned_or_downloaded_dasht/etc/zsh/completions.zsh
.fi
.RE
.PP
Or simply add the completions/ directory to your ZSH $fpath
if you've already set up ZSH's completion system elsewhere:
.PP
.RS
.nf
fpath+=location_where_you_cloned_or_downloaded_dasht/etc/zsh/completions/
.fi
.RE
.SH Usage
.PP
First, install some docsets \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash#docsets\[ra] using 
.BR dasht-docsets-install (1):
.PP
.RS
.nf
dasht\-docsets\-install bash
.fi
.RE
.PP
Next, perform a direct search from the terminal using 
.BR dasht (1):
.PP
.RS
.nf
dasht 'c \- x'
.fi
.RE
.PP
Then, repeat the search in a web browser using 
.BR dasht-server (1):
.PP
.RS
.nf
dasht\-server
.fi
.RE
.PP
You are now ready to use dasht!  Read the manuals below to learn even more.
.SS Manuals
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
You can browse the manuals online at \[la]https://sunaku.github.io/dasht/man/\[ra]\&.
.IP \(bu 2
If you set \fB\fC$MANPATH\fR or installed from a package manager, run \fB\fCman dasht\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
Else, run \fB\fCman \-M location_where_you_cloned_or_downloaded_dasht/man dasht\fR\&.
.RE
.SS Configuration
.PP
You may optionally configure the \fB\fCDASHT_DOCSETS_DIR\fR environment variable,
which defines the filesystem location where your Dash \[la]https://kapeli.com/dash\[ra] docsets are installed.
If undefined, its value is assumed to be \fB\fC$XDG_DATA_HOME/dasht/docsets/\fR or,
if \fB\fCXDG_DATA_HOME\fR is also undefined, \fB\fC$HOME/.local/share/dasht/docsets/\fR\&.
.PP
You may optionally configure the \fB\fCDASHT_CACHE_DIR\fR environment variable,
which defines the filesystem location where download links are cached.
If undefined, its value is assumed to be \fB\fC$XDG_CACHE_HOME/dasht/\fR
or, if \fB\fCXDG_CACHE_HOME\fR is also undefined, \fB\fC$HOME/.cache/dasht/\fR\&.
.SH Development
.PP
If you make changes to the embedded manual pages found in the comment headers
at the top of script files in the \fB\fCbin/\fR directory, then remember to run the
\fB\fCbinman\-rake\fR command afterward to regenerate UNIX manual pages for packaging.
